### Features

New features and changes in this release:

- **Retirement of Azure MySQL and PostgreSQL single server offerings:**
    Azure Database for MySQL - Single Server is on the retirement path and is scheduled for retirement by September 16, 2024.
    Azure Database for PostgreSQL - Single Server is on the retirement path and is scheduled for retirement by March 28, 2025.
    These service offerings are now marked as retired in their marketplace description. 
    After the above dates customers will not be able to create or manage the single server offerings.
    VMware strongly recommends not creating any new instances with this service.
    For more information about the retirement, see the [PostgreSQL Microsoft documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-gb/azure/postgresql/single-server/whats-happening-to-postgresql-single-server) and 
    [MySQL Microsoft documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-gb/azure/mysql/single-server/whats-happening-to-mysql-single-server).

